[01:09.30]	And hugg'd me in his arm, and kindly kiss'd my cheek;
[01:13.17]	Bade me rely on him as on my father,
[01:15.98]	And he would love me dearly as his child.
[01:19.11]DUCHESS OF YORK	Oh, that deceit should steal such gentle shapes,
[01:22.65]	And with a virtuous vizard hide foul guile!
[01:25.93]	He is my son; yea, and therein my shame;
[01:28.86]	Yet from my dugs he drew not this deceit.
[01:32.00]Boy	Think you my uncle did dissemble, grandam?
[01:35.14]DUCHESS OF YORK	Ay, boy.
[01:36.01]Boy	I cannot think it. Hark! what noise is this?
[01:39.21]	[Enter QUEEN ELIZABETH, with her hair about her
[01:39.61]	+ ears; RIVERS, and DORSET after her]
