[01:43.08]	To chide my fortune, and torment myself?
[01:46.09]	I'll join with black despair against my soul,
[01:49.49]	And to myself become an enemy.
[01:51.90]DUCHESS OF YORK	What means this scene of rude impatience?
[01:55.04]QUEEN ELIZABETH	To make an act of tragic violence:
[01:57.71]	Edward, my lord, your son, our king, is dead.
[02:00.84]	Why grow the branches now the root is wither'd?
[02:04.38]	Why wither not the leaves the sap being gone?
[02:07.79]	If you will live, lament; if die, be brief,
[02:10.86]	That our swift-winged souls may catch the king's;
[02:14.53]	Or, like obedient subjects, follow him
[02:17.40]	To his new kingdom of perpetual rest.
[02:20.27]DUCHESS OF YORK	Ah, so much interest have I in thy sorrow
[02:23.41]	As I had title in thy noble husband!
